other_precautions: KEEP CNTNRS TIGHT/UPRIGHT (PREVENT LEAKAGE). NO PROLONGED BREATHING OF VAPORS/SPRAY MISTS. AVOID CONTACT W/SKIN/EYES. DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. DO NOT HANDLE UNTIL THE SAFETY PRECAUTIONS HAVE BEEN READ/ UNDERSTOOD. SMOKE ONLY IN SMOKING AREAS.
protective_equipment: FACE SHIELDS. THE USE OF LONG SLEEVE AND LONG LEG CLOTHING IS RECOMMENDED.
respiratory_protection: USE ORGANIC VAPOR RESPIRATOR (AIR PURIFYING/FRESH AIR). OBSERVE OSHA REGS (RESPIRATOR USE). PROVIDE VENT (KEEP EXPOSURE LEVELS BELOW OSHA LIMITS). VAPOR PARTIC RSPRTR (TC23C--NIOSH/MSHA) IF VAPOR LEVE LS BELOW 10 X EXPOSURE LIMITS.
ventilation: EXHAUST VENT SUFFICIENT TO KEEP AIRBORNE CONC (SOLVENT/ POLYISOCYANATES/HDI) BELOW TLV'S. REMOVE ALL IGNITION SOURCES.
disposal: WASTE MUST BE DISPOSED IN ACCORD W/FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL REGULATIONS. EMPTY CONTAINERS MUST BE HANDLED W/CARE (PRODUCT RESIDUE/FLAMMABLE VAPOR). DON'T INCINERATE CLOSED CNTNRS. EPA HAZARDOUS WASTE #: D001, F003, F005.
extinguishing_media: FOAM, ALCOHOL FOAM, CO2, DRY CHEMICAL, WATER FOG.
fire_fighting: FULL FIRE FIGHT EQUIP W/SCBA & FULL PROTECT CLOTH. USE WATER TO COOL CLOSED CNTNRS/PREVENT PRESSURE BUILD-UP/AUTO IGNITE/EXPLOSION. HDI/IRRIT VAPORS GENERATED.
handling_storage: STORE IN BLDG IN COMPLIANCE W/OSHA 1910.106. AVOID HIGH TEMP, IGNITION SOURCES. STORE IN TIGHTLY CLOSED CONTAINERS. STORE IN WELL VENT AREAS.
spill: EVACUATE ALL NON-ESSENTIAL PERSONNEL. REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION (FLAME, SPARK SOURCES, HOT SURFACES). VENTILATE AREA. CONTAIN AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBENT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

disposal: DISPOSAL MUST BE I/A/W FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL REGULATIONS .

effects_overexposure_skin: skin and eyes.
first_aids_eyes: flush with large amounts of water.
appearance: BATTERY CASE 5.4 IN WIDE X 9.25 IN LONG. 6 VOLTS.
conditions_avoid: AVOID SMOKING, SPARKS, FLAMES, ETC. IN BATTERY CHARGING AREA. AVOID SHORT CIRCUITS,AND MIXING ACID WITH OTHER CHEMICALS.
decomposition_products: SULFUR TRIOXIDE, SULFUR DIOXIDE, HYDOGEN SULFIDE, HYDROGEN GAS.
other_precautions: AVOID MIXING ACID WITH OTHER CHEMICALS. PREVENT SHORT CIRCUITING BATTERY TERMINALS. DO NOT REST TOOLS OR CABLES ON BATTERY. USE INSULATED TOOLS. FOLLOW INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS AND DIAGRAMS WHEN INST ALLING OR MAINTAINING BATTERY SYSTEMS.
protective_equipment: PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT MUST BE WORN IF BATTERY IS CRACKED OR OTHERWISE DAMAGED.
respiratory_protection: NONE UNDER NORMAL CONDITIONS. HEPA RESPIRATOR SHOULD BE WORN DURING BATTERY RECLAIM OPERATIONS, IF THE OSHA PEL IS EXCEEDED.
ventilation: WHEN PEL IS EXCEEDED LOCAL EXHAUST IS PREFERRED. USE ADEQUATE VENTILATION TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURE BELOW PEL.
disposal: NEUTRALIZED ACID MAY BE FLUSHED DOWN SEWER. SPENT LEAD-ACID BATTERIES MAY BE DISPOSED OF BY SENDING TO A LICENSED SECONDARY LEAD SMELTER FOR RECYCLING. USER MUST FOLLOW "DOT" REGULATIONS FOR TRANSPORT ATION. FOLLOW LOCAL,STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE "APC" TYPE FIRE EXTINGUISHER FOR BATTERY FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR FIRE FIGHTING PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT AND A FULL FACED SELF CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. EVACUATE AREA. COOL FIRE EXPOSED CONTAINERS WITH WATER SPRAY.
handling_storage: STORE AWAY FROM REACTIVE MATERIALS, OPEN FLAMES AND SOURCES OF IGNITION. PROHIBIT SMOKING, SPARKS, FLAMES, ETC. FROM BATTERY CHARGING AREA.
spill: NEUTRALIZE ACID WITH SODIUM BICARBONATE (BAKING SODA), SODIUM CARBONATE (SODA ASH) OR CALCIUM OXIDE (LIME). FLUSH AREA WITH WATER, AND DISCARD TO SEWAGE SYSTEM. DO NOT ALLOW UNNEUTRALIZED ACID INTO SE WAGE SYSTEM.

conditions_avoid: OXIDIZING MATERIALS CAN CAUSE A VIGOROUS REACTION.

extinguishing_media: WATER, FOAM, CO*2, DRY CHEMICAL.

extinguishing_media: DRY CHEMICAL OR ALCOHOL TYPE FOAM.
fire_fighting: USE WATERSPRAY TO COOL FIRE EXPOSED SURFACES AND TO PROTECT PERSONNEL. WEAR NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED SCBA AND FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT .

health_hazards_eyes: eye:can cause severe irritation & possible burns,pain,redness,tearing.skin:may cause severe pain,burns & stains.inhaled:fumes/mist may cause severe mucous membrane irritation,coughing,choking,he adache,dizziness & delayed pulmonary edema.ingested:may cause severe burning pain,vomiting,diarrhea.chronic-eye damage.
health_hazards_skin: skin:may cause severe pain,burns & stains.inhaled:fumes/mist may cause severe mucous membrane irritation,coughing,choking,he adache,dizziness & delayed pulmonary edema.ingested:may cause severe burning pain,vomiting,diarrhea.chronic-eye damage.
decomposition_products: THERMAL DECOMPOSITION MAY RELEASE TOXIC FUMES OF AMMONIA, OXIDES OF SULFUR AND NITROGEN
other_precautions: PROTECT CONTAINERS FROM MOISTURE & FROM PHYSICAL DAMAGE.MISUSE OF EMPTY CONTAINERS CAN BE HAZARDOUS.COMPLETELY DRAIN & COMMERCIALLY CLEAN BEFORE REUSE.AVOID CONTACT WITH THE SOLID MATERIAL, SOLUTIONS OR MISTS. IT CAUSES TISSUE DAMAGE.
protective_equipment: IMPERVIOUS APRON, BOOTS, PANTS, HOOD AND JACKET. EYE-WASH FACILITIES, SAFETY SHOWER.
respiratory_protection: IN SITUATIONS WHERE MIST/DUST CONCENTRATIONS MAY EXCEED THE RECOMMENDED EXPOSURE LIMIT, A NIOSH-APPROVED HIGH EFFICIENCY PARTICULATE FILTER RESPIRATOR SHOULD BE WORN. USE SELF-CONTAINED SUPPLIED-AIR R ESPIRATORS FOR EMERGENCIES.
ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION OR CORROSION RESISTANT MECHANICAL VENTILATION OR LOCAL EXHAUST SHOULD BE USED.
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL APPLICABLE LOCAL,STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS. EMPTY TANKS AND CONTAINERS SHOULD BE COMMERCIALLY CLEANED AND RECONDITIONED BEFORE REUSE.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, HALON, OR DRY CHEMICAL. COOL FIRE EXPOSED CONTAINERS WITH WATER.
fire_fighting: IN THE EVENT OF FIRE, WEAR FULL PROTECTIVE CLOTHING & NIOSH-APPROVED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WITH FULL FACEPIECE OPERATED IN POSITIVE PRESSURE MODE.
handling_storage: STORAGE-STORE IN TIGHTLY CLOSED CONTAINERS IN A COOL,DRY,WELL-VENTILATED AREA AWAY FROM BASES & HEAT.
spill: WEAR PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT.VENTILATE AREA.AVOID GENERATION OF DUST/MIST & SPLASHING .DIKE & CONTAIN SPILL.DON'T ALLOW SPILLS TO ENTER SEWERS,STREAM/SURFACE WATER.USE ACID RESISTANT VACUUM/WET SWEEPING TO PICK UP SOLIDS.DILUTE SOLUTIONS & NEUTRALIZE.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: drowsiness, dizziness, fatuge, followed by coma.
first_aids_eyes: eye contact: immediately flush with large amounts of water for 15 minutes.
appearance: VISCOUS LIQUID WITH TYPICAL PAINT ODOR
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE AND CARBON DIOXIDE.
eyes_protection: SAFETY GLASSES W/SIDE SHEILDS OR GOGGLES
other_precautions: MAINTAIN GOOD PERSONAL HYGIENE. DO NOT USE IN CONFINED AREAS, TANK OR PIT, WITHOUT ADEQUATE VENTILATION.
protective_equipment: EYE BATH AND SAFETY SHOWER.
respiratory_protection: IF VENT DOES NOT MAINTAIN INHALE EXPOSURE BELOW TLV (PEL), USE MSHA/NIOSH APPROVED UNITS. USE UNITS PER CURRENT 29CFR1910.134 AND FOLLOW MFRS' INSTRUCTIONS/WARNINGS. IF WITHIN OSHA PROTECTION FACTOR, AIR PURIFYING OV/FILTER UNITS OK USE.
ventilation: LOCAL AND MECHANICAL EXHAUST.
disposal: USE INERT ABSORBENT MATERIALS ON SPILLS. DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGUALTIONS.
extinguishing_media: FOAM, CARBON DIOXIDE, DRY CHEMICAL, WATER FOG.
fire_fighting: APPROVED GAS MASK REQUIRED FOR FIRE FIGHTING PERSONNEL. WATER MAY BE USED TO COOL CONTAINERS. IF WATER IS USED. FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERRED.
handling_storage: CONTAINERS CLOSED/UPRIGHT--PREVENT LEAKAGE. AVOID BREATHING VAPOR AND SPRAY MIST. AVOID SKIN AND EYE CONTACT. AVOID FLAMES, WELDING, OPEN LIGHTS ETC.
spill: STOP LEAK IF NO RISK INVOLVED. REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. STAY UPWIND. ABSORB WITH INERT MATERIAL. FLUSH AREA WITH WATER. VENTILATE AREA FOR AT LEAST 24 HOURS OR UNTIL AREA HAS BEEN DECLARED SAFE .

appearance: CLEAR NEAR WATER WHITE LIQUID; GLYCOL ODOR.
decomposition_products: NONE KNOWN.
other_precautions: CONTAINERS, EVEN THOSE THAT HAVE BEEN EMPTIED WILL RETAIN PRODUCT RESIDUE AND VAPORS. ALWAYS OBEY HAZARD WARNING AND HANDLE EMPTY CONTAINERS AS IF THEY WERE FULL.
protective_equipment: PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AND/OR UNIFORM.
respiratory_protection: UNDER NORMAL CONDITIONS OF USE, NONE IS REQUIRED. IF MISTING EXISTS, USE RESPIRATOR.
ventilation: NONE AS REQUIRED UNDER NORMAL USE CONDITIONS.
disposal: DISPOSE IN ACCORDANCE WITH 42USG3251 ET SEQ RECRA 1976 AND ANY FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: WATER, CO2.
fire_fighting: NONE KNOWN.
handling_storage: STORE AWAY FROM STRONG ACIDS. DO NOT FREEZE.
spill: ADD SAND, EARTH OR OTHER SUITABLE ABSORBENT TO CONTAIN SPILL AREA. NEUTRALIZE WITH MILD ACID, PREVENT FROM DISCHARGE.

first_aids_eyes: flush with plenty of water for at least 15 minutes.
appearance: AMBER COLOR LIQUID. LUBE OIL ODOR.
conditions_avoid: HIGH HEAT, OPEN FLAMES AND OTHER SOURCES OF IGNITION
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE, CARBON DIOXIDE, INCOMPLETELY BURNED CARBON PRODUCTS.
other_precautions: AVOID EYE AND SKIN CONTACT. DO NOT BREATHE VAPORS.
protective_equipment: PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AS REQUIRED TO MINIMIZE EXPOSURE FROM PROLONGED OR REPEATED CONTACT. EYE BATH AND SAFETY SHOWER.
respiratory_protection: NONE NORMALLY REQUIRED. NIOSH/MSHA-APPROVED RESPIRATOR OR SCBA AS APPROPIATE FOR EXPOSURE OF CONCERN.
ventilation: MECHANICAL (GENERAL) VENTILATION OR LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP EXPOSURE LEVELS BELOW PEL.
disposal: CONTACT YOUR LOCAL ENVIRONMENTAL OFFICER. DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS. MANUFACTURER SUGGESTS LANDFILL OR INCINERATION.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: WEAR FIRE FIGHTING PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT AND A FULL FACED SCBA. COOL FIRE EXPOSED CONTAINERS WITH WATER SPRAY. WATER SPRAY MAY BE USED TO FLUSH SPILLS.
handling_storage: STORE IN COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREA. PROTECT FROM PHYSICAL DAMAGE, HEAT, IGNITION SOURCES AND INCOMPATIBLE MATERIALS. KEEP CONTAINERS CLOSED.
spill: REMOVE PERSONNEL. ELIMINATE IGNITION SOURCES. VENTILATE AREA. WEAR PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AND EQUIPMENT. ABSORB IN INERT MATERIAL AND PLACE IN APPROPIATE DISPOSAL CONTAINER AND COVER.

conditions_avoid: CONTACT WITH MOISTURE, MATERIAL WHICH REACT WITH ISOCYANATES AND HIGH TEMPERATURES.
decomposition_products: BY HIGH HEAT/TEMPERATURE: CARBON MONOXIDE, CARBON DIOXIDE, OXIDES OF NITROGEN AND TRACES OF HCN AND HDI.
other_precautions: KEEP UPRIGHT TO PREVENT LEAKAGE. PREVENT PROLONGED OR REPEATED BREATHING OF VAPORS OR SPRAY MISTS. PROLONGED OVEREXPOSURE MAY CAUSE AN ALLERGIC REACTION. AVOID CONTACT W/SKIN & EYES. DO NOT TAKE INTER NALLY.
protective_equipment: USE LONG SLEEVE AND LONG LEG CLOTHING. REMOVE AND WASH CONTAMINATED CLOTHING BEFORE REUSE.
respiratory_protection: RSPRTR RECOMM/APPROVE--USE IN ORGANIC VAPOR ENVIRON (AIR PURIFYING/FRESH AIR). OBSERVE OSHA REGS--RESPIRATOR USE. VENT TO KEEP EXPOSURE LEVELS < OSHA LIMITS. VAPOR PARTIC RSPRTR (TC23C--NIOSH) IF VAPO R LEVELS BELOW 10 X EXPOSURE LEVELS.
ventilation: EXHAUST VENT SUFF TO KEEP AIRBORNE CONC OF SOLVENT, HDI, POLYISOCYANATES BELOW RESPECTIVE TLV'S. REMOVE IGNITE SOURCES.
disposal: IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL REGULATIONS. EMPTY CONTAINERS HANDLE WITH CARE DUE TO PRODUCT RESIDUE & FLAMMABLE VAPOR. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS. SECTION IV, V, VI. EPA HAZARDOUS WASTE # D001, F003, F005.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FULL FIRE FIGHT EQUIP W/SCBA & FULL PROTECT CLOTH. WTR--COOL CLOSED CNTNRS/PREVENT: PRESS BLD-UP/AUTO IGNITE/EXPLOSION. DURING FIRE, HDI/IRRIT VAPORS GENERATED.
handling_storage: STORE IN BUILDINGS DESIGNED TO COMPLY W/OSHA 1910.106. AVOID STORING NEAR IGNITE SOURCES. STORE IN TIGHTLY CLOSED CONTAINRS IN WELL-VENTILATED AREAS.
spill: EVACUATE ALL NONESSENTIAL PERSONNEL. REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION (FLAME, SPARK SOURCES, HOT SURFACES). VENTILATE AREA. CONTAIN AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBENT & NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

first_aids_eyes: flush with water for 15 min holding eyelids open.
appearance: LIGHT AMBER MEDIUM VISCOSITY LIQUID, AROMATIC ESTER SOLVENT ODOR
conditions_avoid: HIGH TEMPERATURES, SPARKS, AND OPEN FLAMES
decomposition_products: CARBON DIOXIDE, CARBON MONOXIDE, OXIDES OF NITROGEN.
other_precautions: PROTECT FROM MOISTURE.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH STATION & SAFETY SHOWER
respiratory_protection: USE NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED RESPIRATOR WHEN SPRAYING OR WHENEVER EXPOSED TO VAPORS/FUMES NEAR OR ABOVE PEL/TLV. SELF CONTAINED RESPIRATOR WITH ORGANIC VAPORS FILTER IS RECOMMENDED.
ventilation: GENERAL VENTILATION SUPPLEMENTED WITH LOCAL EXHAUST, AS NEEDED TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURES BELOW PEL/TLV.
disposal: DISPOSE I/A/W FEDERAL, STATE, AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL, OR WATER FOG. (WATER SPRAY MAY BE INEFFECTIVE.)
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE TIGHTLY CLOSED IN A DRY AREA, FOR FLAMMABLE MATERIALS. APPLY ALL SAFETY PRECAUTIONS TO EMPTY AS WELL AS FULL CONTAINERS.
spill: USE APPROPRIATE PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. VENTILATE AREA AND REMOVE IGNITION SOURCES. COLLECT MATERIAL IN CONTAINERS AND COVER.

decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE
other_precautions: DO NOT PUT DRY ICE IN A CLOSED CONTAINER WHERE EVOLVED GAS CANNOT ESCAPE. USE AN UNSEALED, INSULATED STORAGE CHEST OR CONTAINER FOR DRY ICE. STORE IN A COOL, DARK, WELL-VENTILATED AREA AWAY FROM SOURC ES OF HEAT.
protective_equipment: USE A SAFETY LINE AND STANDBY WORKER WHEN ENTERING CARBON-DIOXIDE ENRICHED AREA. SAFETY SHOES ARE RECOMMENDED.
respiratory_protection: PROVIDE AIR-SUPPLIED OR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING EQUIPMENT FOR EMERGENCY OR NONROUTINE SITUATIONS WHERE THE LEVEL OF CARBON DIOXIDE IS EXCESSIVE.
ventilation: PROVIDE ADEQUATE GENERAL AND LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO PREVENT WORKPLACE ATMOSPHERES FROM BECOMING OXYGEN DEFICIENT.
disposal: REMOVE SCRAP SOLID (DRY ICE), TAKE CYLINDER OUTDOORS OR PLACE IT IN A HOOD WITH GOOD FORCED VENTILATION. ALLOW GAS TO BE DISCHARGED AT A MODERATE RATE. CLOSE VALVE AND RETURN TO SUPPLIER.
extinguishing_media: USE EXTINGUISHING MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE. THIS MAATERIAL CAN BE USED AS AN EXTIGUISHING AGENT.
fire_fighting: WATER MAY BE USED TO INCREASE THE RATE OF EVAPORATION. CARBON DIOXIDE IS A FIRE EXTINGUISHING AGENT BUT MAY NOT BE EFFECTIVE ON CHEMICALS THAT SUPPLY OXYGEN.
handling_storage: HANDLING, STORAGE, AND UTILIZATION OF COMPRESSED-GAS CYLINDERS MUST BE IN ACCORDANCE WITH 29 CFR 1910.101(6). DO NOT STORE THEN IN ENCLOSED AREAS.
spill: NOTIFY SAFETY PERSONNEL OF MAJOR LEAKS OR SPILLS. EVACUATE AREA UNTIL VENTILATION CAN RESTORE A SAFE OXYGEN LEVEL. EMRGENCY PERSONNEL NEED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING EQUIPMENT AND PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AG AINST CONTACT WITH SOLID MATERIAL.

first_aids_eyes: eye-flush with tepid water for 15 minutes.
decomposition_products: NONE
other_precautions: KEEP CONTAINER CLOSED WHEN NOT IN USE TO AVOID PRODUCT EXPOSURE TO ATMOSPHERIC PRESSURE.
protective_equipment: NONE
respiratory_protection: STANDARD DISPOSABLE FOR ORGANIC VAPORS.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST IS SUFFICIENT.
disposal: COVERED LANDFILL. CONTACT YOUR STATE PESTICIDE OR ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL AGENCY OR HAZARDOUS WASTE REPRESENTATIVE AT THE NEAREST EPA REGIONAL OFFICE FOR GUIDLINES. DO NOT CONTAMINATE WATER, FOOD OR FEE D. READ CONTAINER LABEL.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM-TYPE B, POWDER.
fire_fighting: WEAR BREATHING APPARATUS SUCH AS SCOTT AIRPAC.
handling_storage: KEEP AWAY FROM HEAT AND OPEN FLAME.
spill: TAKE UP WITH ABSORBANT FOR ORGANIC LIQUIDS.

first_aids_eyes: do not rub.
appearance: BROWN/GRAY FREE FLOWING AGGREGATE, SLIGHTLY MOIST TO TOUCH, SLIGHT EARTHY ODOR
decomposition_products: NONE KNOWN.
other_precautions: AVOID CONTACT WITH EYES. AVOID CREATING DUST. PROVIDE ADEQUATE VENTILATION AND RESPIRATORY PROTECTION IF NECESSARY. DO NOT USE IN MOISTURE SENSITIVE APPLICATIONS OR WITH WATER REACTIVE MATERIALS.
protective_equipment: NORMAL WORK CLOTHES.
respiratory_protection: NOT GENERALLY REQUIRED. A NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED TYPE TC-21C-XXX DUST RESPIRATOR MAY BE DESIRABLE IF DUST IS CREATED IN HANDLING. HOWEVER, DUST LEVELS ARE EXPECTED TO BE MINIMAL AS LONG AS PRODUCT REMAIN S MOIST.
ventilation: LOCAL AND MECHANICAL (GENERAL) VENTILATION NOT GENERALLY REQUIRED, BUT SHOULD BE USED WHERE AVAILABLE.
disposal: ACCORDING TO EPA (40 CFR 261.3) WASTE OF THIS PRODUCT IS NOT DEFINED AS HAZARDOUS. DISPOSE OF ALL WASTE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL, STATE, AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: MEDIA SUITABLE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE CONDITIONS .
fire_fighting: WEAR NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED SCBA AND FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT .
handling_storage: DISCARD EMPTY PACKAGING PROMPTLY. AVOID EXCESSIVE HANDLING OF EMPTY PACKAGING, WHICH MAY RESULT IN UNNECESSARY RELEASE OF AIRBORNE PARTICULATES.
spill: OBSERVING PRECAUTIONS, SWEEP UP OR SHOVEL SPILLED MATERIAL AND PLACE IN SUITABLE CONTAINERS FOR RECYCLE OR DISPOSAL. DAMPEN WITH WATER SPRAY OR USE OTHER METHODS TO CLEAN SPILL WHICH AVOID CREATING DU ST.

first_aids_eyes: immediately flush eyes with copious amounts of water for at least 15 minutes.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation, ingestion, or skin absorption.
decomposition_products: TOXIC FUMES OF: CARBON MONOXIDE AND CARBON DIOXIDE, NITROGEN OXIDES, HYDROGEN CHLORIDE GAS
eyes_protection: CHEM WORK GOG & FULL LENGTH FCSHLD
other_precautions: DO NT BREATHE DUST. DO NOT GET IN EYES, ON SKIN, ON CLOTHING.

ventilation: MECHANICAL EXHAUST REQUIRED.

extinguishing_media: WATER SPRAY. CARBON DIOXIDE, DRY CHEMICAL POWDER, ALCOHOL OR POLYMER FOAM.
fire_fighting: WEAR NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED SCBA AND FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT
handling_storage: IRRITANT. HARMFUL SOLID. KEEP TIGHTLY CLOSED. MOISTURE SENSITIVE. STORE UNDER NITROGEN. STORE IN COOL DRY PLACE.
spill: WEAR SCBA, RUBBER BOOTS AND HEAVY RUBBER GLOVES. SWEEP UP, PLACE IN A BAG AND HOLD FOR WASTE DISPOSAL. AVOID RAISING DUST. VENTILATE AREA AND WASH SPILL SITE AFTER MATERIAL PICKUP IS COMPLETE.

decomposition_products: NONE UNDER NORMAL CONDITIONS; CARBON DIOXIDE, HCL UNDER THERMAL CONDITIONS.
other_precautions: DO NOT INCINERATE. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN.
protective_equipment: NOT REQUIRED.

disposal: LANDFILL AS PRESCRIBED BY STATE AND LOCAL AUTHORITIES. DISPOSE OF I/A/W FEDERAL, STATE, AND LOCAL REGULATIONS .
extinguishing_media: DRY CHEMICAL, CARBON DIOXIDE OR WATER FOG.

handling_storage: AVOID STORAGE AT EXTREMES IN TEMPERATURES.
spill: ALLOW MATERIAL TO CURE; DISPOSE IN LANDFILL.

spill: STOP LEAK IF NO RISK INVOLVED. STAY UPWIND. SM SPILLS:ABSORB W/SAND/OTHER NONCOMBUST ABSORB MATL. FLUSH AREA W/WATER. DIKE LRG SPILLS FOR LATER DISP. THIS PROD RELEASED IN ENVIRON MUST BE REPORTED TO THE NATIONAL RESPONSE CENTER (1-800-424-8802).

spill: SE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION;CONTAIN FREE MATERIAL IF POSSIBLE;USE SUITABLE INERT ABSORBENT MATERIAL AND RECOVER FOR PROPER DISPOSAL IN AN APPROVED CONTAINER.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: headache, weakness, dizziness, incoordination and possible unconsciousness or coma.
first_aids_inhalation: remove from exposure, restore breathing if stopped.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation: irritation of the respiratory tract and acute nervous system depression.
appearance: GRAY VISCOUS LIQUID WITH A TYPICAL SOLVENT ODOR.
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE, CARBON DIOXIDE UPON THERMAL DECOMPOSITION.
other_precautions: KEEP CONTAINERS CLOSED WHEN MATERIAL IS NOT IN USE. GROUND AND BOND DRUMS. DO NOT USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY DRUMS. KEEP AWAY FROM HEAT AND OPEN FLAME. DISCARD CONTAMINATED FOOTWEAR. DO NOT WEAR CONTAMINAT ED CLOTHING. MAINTAIN GOOD HOUSEKEEPING.
protective_equipment: WEAR INDUSTRIAL-TYPE WORK CLOTHING AND SAFETY FOOTWEAR. WEAR PROTECTIVE APRONS, COVERALLS, HATS ETC. AS REQUIRED.
respiratory_protection: OUTDOORS: NIOSH APPROVED RESPIRATOR FOR PAINT, ENAMEL MISTS, & ORGANIC VAPORS. RESTRICTED VENTILATION AREAS: APPROVED CHEMICAL/MECHANICAL FILTERS DESIGNED TO REMOVE A COMBINATION OF PARTICULATES & VAP OR. CONFINED AREAS: AIR LINE RESPIRATOR.
ventilation: GENERAL/LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO CONTROL INHALATION EXPOSURE BELOW PEL. LOCAL REQUIRED FOR ENCLOSED/CONFINED SPACES.
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN A MANNER THAT COMPLIES WITH LOCAL, STATE, AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS. INCINERATE IN APPROVED FACILITY. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN A COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREA OR BUILDING WHICHCOMPLIES WITH OSHA 1910.106. KEEP IN A CLOSED, LABELED CONTAINER. PROTECT FROM DAMAGE.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS. VENTILATE AREA. AVOID CONTACT WITH HOT LIQUID AND FUMES. CONTAIN AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBENT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS. REACTS WITH OXIDIZING M ATERIALS. RQ IS 100 LBS OR MORE.

first_aids_eyes: eye contact: flush with water 15 minutes or until irritation subsides.
appearance: LIGHT GRAY LIQUID WITH KEROSENE ODOR.
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE.
protective_equipment: USE CHEM RESISTANT APRON OR CLOTHING TO AVOID REPEATED SKIN CONTACT. SEE 29CFR1910.1025 FOR OCCUPATIONAL LEAD EXPOSURE.
respiratory_protection: USE HYDROCARBON VAPOR CANISTER OR SUPPLIED AIR RESPIRATOR IN CONFINED AREAS. USE RESPIRATORY PROTECTION AGAINST LEAD DUST DURING SANDING.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST: FACE VELOCITY 60FPM. SPECIAL: USE ONLY W/ADEQUATE VENTILATION. MECHANICAL: USE EXPLOSION PROOF EQUIPMENT.
disposal: ASSURE CONFORMITY WITH APPLICABLE DISPOSAL REGULATIONS. DISPOSE OF ABSORBED MATERIAL AT AN APPROVED DISPOSAL SITE OR FACILITY.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, WATER FOG OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: USE AIR SUPPLIED BREATHING EQUIPMENT. COOL ENCLOSED CONTAINERS WITH WATER SPRAY. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS OR FUMES. .
spill: REMOVE ALL IGNITION SOURCES. KEEP FROM HEAT, SPARKS AND OPEN FLAME. ADD ABSORBENT (SAND, EARTH, SAWDUST) TO SPILL. VENTILATE AREA (OPEN WINDOWS, DOORS). LARGE SPILL: KEEP FROM ENTERING SEWERS/WATERCOU RSES BY DIKING. ADVISE AUTHORITIES IF DOES ENTER.

conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, INCLUDING WHEN HEATED BY WELD/CUTTING, WILL PRODUCESMOKE, CARBON MONOXIDE AND CARBON DIOXIDE.
other_precautions: KEEP AWAY FROM CHILDREN. EMPTY CONTAINERS MUST NOT BE WASHED & RE-USED FOR ANY PURPOSE. CONTAINERS SHOULD BE GROUND/BONDED TO RECEIVING CONTAINERS. DON'T WELD/CUT ON EMPTY CONTAINER. NEVER USE PRESSU RE TO EMPTY, DRUM IS NOT PRESSURE VESSEL
protective_equipment: NOT LIKELY TO BE NEEDED.
respiratory_protection: MECHANICAL PREFILTER MAY BE REQUIRED. CONFINED AREAS; NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED AIR SUPPLIED RESPIRATOR. TLV EXCEEDED USE PROPERLY FITTED NIOSH/MSHA RESPIRATOR WITHAPPROPRIATE PROTECT FACTOR. REFER TO OSH A 29 CFR 1910.134 RESPIRATORY PROTECTION
ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION & LOCAL EXHAUST VENT SUFFICIENT VOL/PATTERNTO KEEP HAZARD INGRED BELOW LOWEST EXPOS LIMIT/REMOVE DECOMP
disposal: INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA PERMITTED FACILITY. DON'T INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAIN. OBSERVE PRECAUTIONS FORDISPOSAL OF FLAMMABLE MATERIAL. CONTAM ABSORBANT DISPOSE IN HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL. ONLY IN ACCOR DANCE WITH FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: NFPA CLASS B FIRE EXTING. CARBON DIOXIDE, ALL PURPOSE DRY CHEM, ALCOHOL FOAM, FOR EXTING FLAMM LIQ FIRES. POLYMER FOAM
fire_fighting: WEAR SCBA. WATER MAY INEFFECTIVE, BUT USED TO COOL EXPOSED CONTAINERS, PREVENT PRESSURE BUILD-UP/AUTO-IGNITE/EXPLOSION FROM EXTREME HEAT. FOG NOZZLES PREFERED.
handling_storage: DON'T STORE ABOVE 95 DEG F. STORE LARGE QUANTITIESIN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29FR1910.106. DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. CLOSE CONTAINER AFTER EACH USE.
spill: KEEP SPECTATORS AWAY. ELIMINATE ALL IGNITE SOURCESFLAMES,HOT SURFACE, ETC. DIKE & CONTAIN SPILL WITHINERT MATERIAL(SAND,EARTH).TRANSFER LIQ TO COVEREDMETAL CONTAINERS FOR RECOVERY/DISPOSAL. REMOVE W/ INERT ABSORBENT. USE ONLY NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

other_precautions: AVOID EYE, SKIN CONTACT, INHALATION, INGESTION OF MIST, SPRAY OR VAPORS. AVOID BREATHING SANDING OR BLASTING DUST.

first_aids_eyes: immediately flush with plenty of water for at least 15 minutes.see doctor.
conditions_avoid: POLYMERIZES EASILY. AVOID TEMPERATURES ABOVE 90F. MAINTAIN INHIBITOR AND DISSOLVED OXYGEN LEVEL.
decomposition_products: CARBON DIOXIDE, CARBON MONOXIDE, INCOMPLETELY BURNED CARBON PRODUCTS.
eyes_protection: CHEMICAL GOGGLES OR FULL FACE RESPIRATOR
other_precautions: NONE.
protective_equipment: IMPERVIOUS PROTECTIVE CLOTHING. USE OF BOOTS, APRON OR FULL-BODY SUIT WILL DEPEND ON TYPE OF OPERATION.
respiratory_protection: ATMOSPHERIC LEVELS SHOULD BE MAINTAINED BELOW THE EXPOSURE GUIDELINE. WHEN RESPIRATORY PROTECTION IS REQUIRED FOR CERTAIN OPERATIONS, USE AN APPROVED AIR-PURIFYING RESPIRATOR.
ventilation: MECHANICAL (GENERAL) VENTILATION IS REQUIRED. LOCAL EXHAUST MAY BE REQUIRED IF WORK AREA IS NOT VENTED.
disposal: INCINERATE IN PROPERLY DESIGNED FURNACE. DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL LAWS AND REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREA. PROTECT FROM PHYSICAL DAMAGE, HEAT AND IGNITION SOURCES. KEEP CONTAINERS CLOSED.
spill: ABSORB WITH SUITABLE AGENT, SUCH AS SAND OR VERMICULITE.WASH AREA WITH SOAP AND WATER. SOME ABSORBENTS SUCH AS ZORB-ALL MAY INITIATE POLYMERIZATION.

respiratory_protection: DO NOT BREATHE VAPORS OR MISTS. WEAR A NIOSH/MSHA (TC-23C) FOR USE WITH PAINTS DURING APPLICATION AND UNTIL ALL VAPORS AND SPRAY MISTS ARE EXHAUSTED. FOLLOW THE RESPIRATOR MANUFACTURER'S DIRECTIONS FOR RESPIRATOR USE.
ventilation: SUFFICIENT VENT IN VOL/PATTERN, TO KEEP CONTAM BELOW APPLI- CABLE OSHA REQUIREMENTS AND OTHER SUGGESTED EXPOSURE LIMITS.
disposal: DO NOT ALLOW MATERIAL TO CONTAMINATE GROUND WATER SYSTEMS. INCINERATE ABSORBED MATERIAL IN ACCORD- ANCE WITH FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REQUIREMENTS. DO NOT INCINERATE IN CLOSED CONTAINERS.
extinguishing_media: FOAM, CARBON DIOXIDE, DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT, INCLUDING SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS, IS RE- COMMENDED. WATER FROM FOG NOZZLES MAY BE USED TO PREVENT PRESSURE BUILD-UP.
handling_storage: OBSERVE LABEL PRECAUTIONS. KEEP AWAY FROM HEAT, SPARKS AND FLAME. CLOSE CONTAINER AFTER EACH USE. GROUND CONTAINERS WHEN POURING.
spill: VENTILATE AREA. REMOVE SOURCES OF IGNITION. PRE- VENT SKIN CONTACT AND BREATHING OF VAPOR. CONFINE AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBENT.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation.
first_aids_eyes: eye contact: flush with water 15 minutes or until irritation subsides.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation.
appearance: DARK GRAY LIQUID WITH ALCOHOL ODOR.
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE.
other_precautions: AVOID EYE, SKIN CONTACT, INHALATION &/OR INGESTION OF MISTS, SPRAY OR VAPORS. AVOID BREATHING SANDING OR BLASTING DUST.
protective_equipment: USE CHEMICAL RESISTANT APRON OR CLOTHING.
respiratory_protection: USE HYDROCARBON VAPOR CANISTER OR SUPPLIED AIR RESPIRATOR IN CONFINED AREAS.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST: FACE VELOCITY 60FPM. SPECIAL: USE ONLY W/ADEQUATE VENTILATION. MECHANICAL: USE EXPLOSION PROOF EQUIPMENT.
disposal: ASSURE CONFORMITY WITH APPLICABLE DISPOSAL REGULATIONS. DISPOSE OF ABSORBED MATERIAL AT AN APPROVED DISPOSAL SITE OR FACILITY. DISPOSE IN CONFORMITY WITH STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, WATER FOG OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: USE AIR SUPPLIED BREATHING EQUIPMENT. COOL ENCLOSED CONTINERS WITH WATER SPRAY. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS OR FUMES. .
handling_storage: STORE AWAY FROM IGNITION SOURCES, KEEP IN COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREAS. AVOID DIRECT SUNLIGHT AND EXTREME TEMPERATURES, HOT OR COLD.
spill: REMOVE ALL IGNITION SOURCES. KEEP FROM HEAT, SPARKS AND OPEN FLAME. ADD ABSORBENT (SAND, EARTH, SAWDUST) TO SPILL. VENTILATE AREA (OPEN WINDOWS, DOORS). LARGE SPILL: KEEP FROM ENTERING SEWERS/WATERCOU RSES BY DIKING. ADVISE AUTHORITIES IF DOES ENTER.

other_precautions: DO NOT REUSE EMPTY CONTAINER. DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. CONTAINER SHOULD BE GROUNDED AND BONDED TO THE RECEIVING CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD/BRAZE OR CUT CONT'R.NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. DRUM IS NOT A PRESSURE VESSEL. CLOSE AFTER EA USE.
protective_equipment: NOT LIKELY TO BE NEEDED.
respiratory_protection: WELL VENTILATED AREA-RESP NOT REQ. RESTRICTED VENT-NIOSH CHEMICAL CARTRIDGE MAY BE REQ. IF SPRAYING, MECH PREFILTER MAY BE REQ. IF TLV ARE EXCEEDED, USE A PROP FITTED NIOSH/MSHA RESP W/APPROP PROTECTI ON FACTOR. SEE OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134.

extinguishing_media: USE NFPA CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. WATER TO COOL CONT TO PREVENT POSSIBLE AUTO-IGNITION OR EXPLOSION. IF WATER IS USED, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERABLE.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 95 DEGREES F. STORE LARGE QUANITIES IN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29CFR1910.106.

disposal: DUST SHOULD BE HANDLED AS A HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANT I/A/W 40CFR61 SUBPART "M" PERTAINING TO ASBESTOS. USE LANDFILLS APPROVED FOR ASBESTOS DISPOSAL. NOTE IF ITEM UNDER CONSIDERATION FOR DISPOSAL IS "FRIABLE OR NON-FRIABLE".

health_hazards_eyes: eyes may cause irritation and/or burns.
health_hazards_skin: skin and eyes may cause irritation and/or burns.
appearance: TAN PELLETS OR TRISIV GRANULES OR BEADS, OR WHITE POWDER OR CAKE; ODORLESS.
conditions_avoid: THE ADDITION OF MOISTURE/WATER W/O FLOODING CAN CAUSE RISE OF TEMEPRATURE FROM HEAT OF ADSORPTION-MAY CAUSE SKIN BURNS.
decomposition_products: MIXTURE OF OXIDES OF INGREDIENTS.
other_precautions: DO NOT PUT IN MOUTH OR POUR LIQUID INTO PRODUCT; BURNS MAY RESULT. DUST MAY IRRITATE EYES, NOSE, THROAT AND SKIN.
respiratory_protection: IF ENGINEERING CONTROLS FAIL OR NON-ROUTINE USE OR AN EMERGENCY OCCURS; WEAR AN MSHA/NIOSH APPROVED RESPIRATOR WITH DUST CARTRIDGE OR AN AIR-SUPPLIED RESPIRATOR OR SCBA, AS REQUIRED. USE IAW 29 CFR 19 10.134.
ventilation: USE ADEQUATE MECHANICAL VENTILATION OR LOCAL EXHAUST TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURE BELOW TLV(S).
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL ENVIRONMENTAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS AND FULL PROTECTIVE GERA.
handling_storage: USE WITH ADEQUATE VENTILATION. OPEN CONTAINER SLOWLY. AVOID BREATHING DUST. AVOID CONTACT WITH EYES AND SKIN.
spill: SWEEP UP THE SPILL AREA. COLLECT AND PLACE THE SPILLED MATERIAL IN A WASTE DISPOSAL CONTAINER. AVOID RAISING DUST.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eyes, mucous membranes, stupor, drying of skin
health_hazards_ingestion: ingestion: can cause headache, drowsiness & unconsciousness.inhalation: vapors are irritating to nasal passages and throat.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation: vapors are irritating to nasal passages and throat.
conditions_avoid: HIGH TEMPERATURES, SPARKS, AND OPEN FLAMES
decomposition_products: SMOKE,SOOT,OXIDES OF CARBON ON COMBUSTION
other_precautions: DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. DO NOT BREATHE MIST. AVOID PROLONGED OR REPEATED BREATHING OF VAPOR. AVOID CONTACT WITH EYES. USE WITH ADEQUATE VENTILATION. WASH THOROUGHLY AFTER HANDLING. USE SPARK-RESISTANT TOOLS.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH STATION AND SAFETY SHOWER. INDUSTRIAL-TYPE WORK CLOTHING, APRON, AND BOOTS IF SPILLS OR SPLASHING CAN OCCUR.
respiratory_protection: IF VENTILATION DOES NOT MAINTAIN INHALATION EXPOSURES BELOW PEL(TLV), USE NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED FULL-FACE ORGANIC VAPOR CARTRIDGE OR CANISTER RESPIRATORS AS PER CURRENT 29 CFR 1910.134, INSTRUCTIONS/WAR NINGS AND NIOSH-RESPIRATOR SELECTION.
ventilation: MECHANICAL (GENERAL) ROOM VENTILATION AND LOCAL EXHAUST BOTH REQUIRED.
disposal: DISPOSAL SHOULD BE MADE BY INCINERATION IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL LAWS AND REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN A COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREA AWAY FROM SOURCES OF IGNITION. KEEP CONTAINERS TIGHTLY CLOSED WHEN NOT IN USE. STORE BELOW 130 DEG. F.
spill: SMALL SPILL: WIPE/SOAK UP WITH PAPER TOWEL OR INERT ABSORBANT. PUT IN DISPOSAL CONTAINER. REMOVE RESIDUE WITH WATER. LARGE SPILL: EVACUATE AND VENTILATE AREA. IF POSSIBLE, STOP LEAK. DIKE TO RETAIN RU N OFF. VACUUM UP FREE LIQUID. ABSORB/WASH RESIDUE.

ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION OR LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP TWA/LEL BELOW ACCEPTABLE LIMITS & TO REMOVE DECOMPOSITION PRODUCTS
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
handling_storage: CONTAINERS SHOULD BE GROUNDED WHEN POURING. AVOID FREE FALL OF LIQUID IN EXCESS OF A FEW INCHES. DRUM SHOULD BE INDUSTRIALLY CLEANED PRIOR TO REUSE.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS. VENTILATE AREA AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBANT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, INCLUDING WHEN HEATED BY WELDING OR CUTTING, WILL PRODUCE SMOKE, CARBON MONOXIDE AND CARBON DIOXIDE.
other_precautions: DO NOT REUSE EMPTY CONTAINER. DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. CONTAINER SHOULD BE GROUNDED AND BONDED TO THE RECEIVING CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD/BRAZE OR CUT CONT'R.NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. DRUM IS NOT A PRESSURE VESSEL. CLOSE AFTER EA USE.
protective_equipment: NOT LIKELY TO BE NEEDED.
respiratory_protection: WELL VENTILATED AREA-RESP NOT REQ. RESTRICTED VENT-NIOSH CHEMICAL CARTRIDGE MAY BE REQ. IF SPRAYING, MECH PREFILTER MAY BE REQ. IF TLF ARE EXCEEDED, USE A PROP FITTED NIOSH/MSHA RESP W/APPROP PROTECTI ON FACTOR. SEE OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134.
ventilation: PROVIDE DILUTION/LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP CONCEN- TRATIONS OF HAZARDOUS INGRID BELOW EXPOSURE LIMITS STATED.
disposal: INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA PERMITTED FACILITY. DISPOSEONLY IAW FED/STATE/LOCAL REGS. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS. OBSERVE PRECAUTIONS FOR DIS- POSAL OF FLAMMABLE MAT'S. CONTAMINATED ABSORBENT MAY BE DISPOSED IN A HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL.
extinguishing_media: USE NFPA CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. WATER TO COOL CONT TO PREVENT POSSIBLE AUTO-IGNITION OR EXPLOSION. IF WATER IS USED, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERABLE.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 95F. STORE LARGE QUANTITIES IN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29CFR1910.106.
spill: ELIM ALL IGNITION SOURCES. DIKE/CONTAIN SPILL WITHINERT MAT'L. TRANSFER LIQ'S/ABSORBENT DIKING MAT'LIN COVERED METAL CONT'S FOR RECOVERY/DISPOSAL. USEONLY NON-SPARKING TOOLS. PREVENT CONTAM OF SEWERS/ STREAMS/GROUNDWATER W/SPILLED MAT'L/USED ABSORBENT

effects_overexposure_eyes: eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation of airborne dust containing asbestos fibers on repeated exposure may cause or can lead to asbestosis / mesothelioma; skin: n/k; eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
effects_overexposure_skin: skin: n/k; eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
eyes_protection: SAFETY GLASSES W/SIDE SHIELDS OR GOGGLES
other_precautions: AS MANUFACTURED, LOCKED-IN ASBESTOS DOES NOT PRESENT A HAZARD. ONLY WHEN THE ITEM IS SUBJECTED TO ABRASIVE ACTIONS & DUST IS GENERATED, THEN ASBESTOS FIBERS MAY BE RELEASED & BECOME AIRBORNE.
protective_equipment: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND, AND THE GUIDANCE SET FORTH BY YOUR SAFETY OFFICE OR IH PERSONNEL
protective_gloves: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND.
respiratory_protection: IF EXPOSURES EXCEED ESTABLISHED LIMITS, A NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED RESPIRATOR FOR ASBESTOS SHOULD BE USED. CONSULT YOUR SAFETY OFFICE/IH PERSONNEL FOR GUIDANCE FOR THE TASK AT HAND.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST IS RECOMMENDED IN SITUATIONS WHERE DUST IS GENERATED BY ABRASIVE ACTIONS, ABRASION OR OTHER MEANS.
disposal: DUST SHOULD BE HANDLED AS A HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANT I/A/W 40CFR61 SUBPART "M" PERTAINING TO ASBESTOS. USE LANDFILLS APPROVED FOR ASBESTOS DISPOSAL. NOTE IF ITEM UNDER CONSIDERATION FOR DISPOSAL IS "FRIABLE OR NON-FRIABLE".
extinguishing_media: MATERIAL IS NOT FLAMMABLE ; USE MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE.
fire_fighting: COMBUSTION PRODUCTS OF THIS MATERIAL MAY BE TOXIC. USE A SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WHEN FIGHTING FIRES INVOLVING CHEMICAL PRODUCTS.
handling_storage: HANDLE IN A MATTER TO MINIMIZE FORMATION OR RETENTION OF AIRBORNE DUST. USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION FOR TASK AT HAND. CHECK W/YOUR SAFETY OFFICE!!!
spill: USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION. VACUUM OR WET CLEAN IF DUST IS INVOLVED. ANY VACUUM SYSTEM SHOULD BE EQUIPPED W/ AN OUTLET "HEPA" FILTER TO PREVENT REINTRODUCING ASBESTOS FIBERS TO THE ATMOSPHERE.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation may cause irritation of the respiratory tract, headaches, dizziness or drowsiness.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation may cause irritation of the respiratory tract, headaches, dizziness or drowsiness.
conditions_avoid: WILL REACT W/WATER OR WATER CONTAINING PRODUCT, GIVE OFF HEAT/FUMES. DON'T ALLOW WATER TO ENTER SEALED DRUM, MAY EXPLODE
decomposition_products: FUMES MAY CONTAIN CARBON MONOXIDE & OXIDES OF NITROGEN. MAY PRODUCE HAZARDOUS FUMES WHEN HEATED TO DECOMP AS IN WELDING.
eyes_protection: SAFETY EYEWARE TO PROTECT AGAINST SPLASH
other_precautions: MAKE SURE DRUM IS COMPLETELY EMPTY BEFORE ATTEMPTING TO WELD OR BRAZE. DRUM SHOULD BE INDUSTRIALLY CLEANED PRIOR TO REUSE. DO NOT FLAME CUT, BRAZE OR WELD WITHOUT A NIOSH APPROVED RESPIRATOR OR APPROP RIATE VENTILATION.
respiratory_protection: DO NOT BREATHE VAPOR OR MIST. USE NIOSH/MSHA TC19C AIR LINE RESPIRATOR OR TC23C VAPOR/PARTICULATE RESPIRATOR IF ISOCYANATES ARE 10 X LESS THAN TLV.
ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION OR LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP TWA/LEL BELOW ACCEPTABLE LIMITS & TO REMOVE DECOMPOSITION PRODUCTS
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
handling_storage: CONTAINERS SHOULD BE GROUNDED WHEN POURING. AVOID FREE FALL OF LIQUID IN EXCESS OF A FEW INCHES.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS. VENTILATE AREA AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBANT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

first_aids_eyes: flush w/water 15 min hold lids open.
decomposition_products: CARBON DIOXIDE, CARBON MONOXIDE, TRACES ON HYDROGEN CYANIDE, OXIDES OF NITROGEN, TOLUENE DIISOCYANATE.
other_precautions: 'EMPTY' CONTAINERS MAY CONTAIN RESIDUE OR VAPOR. TREAT THEM WITH THE RESPECT DUE FULL ONES. DO NOT CUT,WELD,ETC. ON THEM.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH STATION & SAFETY SHOWER. COVER AS MUCH SKIN AS POSSIBLE DURING OPERATIONS.
respiratory_protection: USE POSITIVE PRESSURE AIR SUPPLIED RESPIRATOR ANY TIME THE EXPOSURE IS ABOVE THE CEILING, SHORT TERM EXPOSURE LEVEL,OR PEL, AND AT ALL TIMES DURING SPRAYING OPERATIONS. OTHER RESPIRATORS MAY BE USED F OR SHORT (1 HOUR) EXPOSURES ONLY!!
ventilation: GENERAL VENTILATION SUPPLEMENTED WITH LOCAL EXHAUST, AS NEEDED TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURES BELOW PEL/TLV.
disposal: DISPOSE I/A/W FEDERAL,STATE,LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE TIGHTLY CLOSED IN A DRY AREA. STORE BETWEEN 32-122F (50-81F, IDEAL). PROTECT FROM MOISTURE. PRODUCT WILL POLYMERIZE SLOWLY AT HIGHER TEMPERATURE
spill: ALWAYS USE APPROPRIATE PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. COVER SPILL WITH SAWDUST,VERMICULITE,ETC. ADD LIQUID DECONTAMINANT AND ALLOW TO SET FOR AT LEAST 10 MIN. COLLECT MATERIAL IN OPEN CONTAINERS AND ADD MORE DECONTAMINANT.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eyes, skin, respiratory and gastrointestinal tracts irritation, headache, dizziness, nausea, vomiting, defatting and drying skin
effects_overexposure_skin: skin, respiratory and gastrointestinal tracts irritation, headache, dizziness, nausea, vomiting, defatting and drying skin
health_hazards_eyes: eye/skin contact may cause moderate to severe irritation.
health_hazards_skin: skin contact may cause moderate to severe irritation.
conditions_avoid: HEAT, SPARKS, OPEN FLAMES HOT SURFACES, STATIC ELECTRICITY
decomposition_products: MAY FORM CARBON MONOXIDE, CARBON DIOXIDE AND OTHER TOXIC VOLATILE ORGANIC COMPOUNDS.
other_precautions: "EMPTY" CONTAINERS RETAIN RESIDUE AND CAN BE DANGEROUS. DO NOT PRESSURIZE, CUT, WELD, BRAZE, SOLDER, DRILL OR EXPOSE SUCH CONTAINERS TO HEAT, FLAME, SPARKS. THEY MAY EXPLODE AND CAUSE INJURY/DEATH. AV OID REPEATED OR PROLONGED SKIN CONTACT.
protective_equipment: IMPERVIOUS CLOTHING AND EQUIPMENT TO PREVENT REPEATEE OR PROLONGED CONTACT. EYEWASH STATION, EMERGENCY SHOWER
respiratory_protection: IF WORKING IN A CONFINED AREA OR TLV IS EXCEEDED, USE NIOSH-APPROVED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS OR SUPPLIED AIR RESPIRATOR WITH FULL FACEPIECE, OPERATED IN POSITIVE PRESSURE MODE.
ventilation: MECHANICAL (GENERAL AND/OR LOCAL EXHAUST, EXPLOSION-PROOF) VENTILATION TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURE BELOW TLV(S).
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS. IF POSSIBLE, TRANSFER TO RECLAIMING CENTER FOR RECYCLING OR REUSE.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM/DRY CHEMICAL. WATER SPRAY MAY BE USED TO KEEP FIRE EXPOSED CONTAINERS COOL & FLUSH SPILLS AWAY.
fire_fighting: WEAR FULL PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AND NIOSH-APPROVED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WITH FULL FACEPIECE OPERATED IN THE POSITIVE PRESSURE MODE.
handling_storage: STORE IN COOL, VENTILATED AREA, AWAY FROM INCOMPATIBLES. METAL CONTAINERS SHOULD BE FITTED WITH A BONDED GROUND WIRE WHEN MATERIAL IS TRANSFERRED.
spill: WEAR PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. REMOVE IGNITION SOURCES. VENTILATE AREA. PICK UP SPILL WITH PUMP/NON-FLAMMABLE ABSORBENT MATERIAL SUCH AS SAND. PLACE IN CONTAINER FOR DISPOSAL. PREVENT LIQUID FROM ENTERING SEWERS, WATERWAYS OR LOW AREAS. WASH SPILL SITE.

decomposition_products: INCOMPLETE COMBUSTION CAN YIELD LOW MOLECULAR WEIGHT HYDROCARBONS,CARBON MONOXIDE,NITROGEN COMPOUNDS,SULFUR COMPOUNDS.
other_precautions: AVOID SKIN CONTACT WITH PRODUCT AT ALL TIMES.
protective_equipment: APPROPRIATE PROTECTIVE CLOTHING TO PREVENT CONTACT.
respiratory_protection: NOT NORMALLY REQUIRED.
ventilation: STANDARD INDUSTRIAL VENTILATION.
disposal: DISP MUST BE IAW FED,STATE & LOC REGS.COORDINATION W/ SUPPORTING INSTALLATION &/OR MACOM ENVIRON COORDINATION PRIOR TO DISP IS RECOMND PRIOR TO DISP TO DETERMINE APPROP DISP METH .INCINERATE OR DISPOSE OF IN AN APPROP INDUSTRIAL LANDFILL.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER SPRAY,FOAM,DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
fire_fighting: PERSONS EXPOSED TO PRODUCTS OF COMBUSTION SHOULD WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS AND FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT.
handling_storage: STORE IN A COOL,DRY LOCATION.
spill: WEAR RUBBER GLOVES AND WIPE UP WITH ABSORBENT MATERIAL.RESIDUE MAY BE REMOVED WITH CHLORINATED SOLVENT.

first_aids_eyes: flush w/water 15 min hold lids open.
conditions_avoid: TEMPERATURES IN EXCESS OF THOSE PUBLISHED IN THE PRODUCT LITERATURE.
decomposition_products: CARBON DIOXIDE, CARBON MONOXIDE, TRACES ON HYDROGEN CYANIDE, OXIDES OF NITROGEN, TOLUENE DIISOCYANATE.
other_precautions: 'EMPTY' CONTAINERS MAY CONTAIN RESIDUE OR VAPOR. TREAT THEM WITH THE RESPECT DUE FULL ONES. DO NOT CUT,WELD,ETC. ON THEM.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH STATION & SAFETY SHOWER. COVER AS MUCH SKIN AS POSSIBLE DURING OPERATIONS.
respiratory_protection: USE POSITIVE PRESSURE AIR SUPPLIED RESPIRATOR ANY TIME THE EXPOSURE IS ABOVE THE CIELING, SHORT TERM EXPOSURE LEVEL,OR PEL, AND AT ALL TIMES DURING SPRAYING OPERATIONS. OTHER RESPIRATORS MAY BE USED F OR SHORT (1 HOUR) EXPOSURES ONLY!!
ventilation: GENERAL VENTILATION SUPPLEMENTED WITH LOCAL EXHAUST, AS NEEDED TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURES BELOW PEL/TLV.
disposal: DISPOSE I/A/W FEDERAL,STATE,LOCAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL, OR WATER FOG.
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE TIGHTLY CLOSED IN A DRY AREA. STORE BETWEEN 32-122F (50-81F, IDEAL). PROTECT FROM MOISTURE. PRODUCT WILL POLYMERIZE SLOWLY AT HIGHER TEMPERATURE
spill: ALWAYS USE APPROPRIATE PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. COVER SPILL WITH SAWDUST,VERMICULITE,ETC. ADD LIQUID DECONTAMINANT AND ALLOW TO SET FOR AT LEAST 10 MIN. COLLECT MATERIAL IN OPEN CONTAINERS AND ADD MORE DECONTAMINANT.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation of airborne dust containing asbestos fibers on repeated exposure may cause or can lead to asbestosis / mesothelioma; skin: n/k; eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
effects_overexposure_skin: skin: n/k; eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.
eyes_protection: SAFETY GLASSES W/SIDE SHIELDS OR GOGGLES
other_precautions: AS MANUFACTURED, LOCKED-IN ASBESTOS DOES NOT PRESENT A HAZARD. ONLY WHEN THE ITEM IS SUBJECTED TO ABRASIVE ACTIONS & DUST IS GENERATED, THEN ASBESTOS FIBERS MAY BE RELEASED & BECOME AIRBORNE.
protective_equipment: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND, AND THE GUIDANCE SET FORTH BY YOUR SAFETY OFFICE OR IH PERSONNEL
protective_gloves: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND.
respiratory_protection: IF EXPOSURES EXCEED ESTABLISHED LIMITS, A NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED RESPIRATOR FOR ASBESTOS SHOULD BE USED. CONSULT YOUR SAFETY OFFICE/IH PERSONNEL FOR GUIDANCE FOR THE TASK AT HAND.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST IS RECOMMENDED IN SITUATIONS WHERE DUST IS GENERATED BY ABRASIVE ACTIONS, ABRASION OR OTHER MEANS.
disposal: DUST SHOULD BE HANDLED AS A HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANT I/A/W 40CFR61 SUBPART "M" PERTAINING TO ASBESTOS. USE LANDFILLS APPROVED FOR ASBESTOS DISPOSAL. NOTE IF ITEM UNDER CONSIDERATION FOR DISPOSAL IS "FRIABLE OR NON-FRIABLE".
extinguishing_media: MATERIAL IS NOT FLAMMABLE ; USE MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE.
fire_fighting: COMBUSTION PRODUCTS OF THIS MATERIAL MAY BE TOXIC. USE A SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WHEN FIGHTING FIRES INVOLVING CHEMICAL PRODUCTS.
handling_storage: HANDLE IN A MATTER TO MINIMIZE FORMATION OR RETENTION OF AIRBORNE DUST. USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION FOR TASK AT HAND. CHECK W/YOUR SAFETY OFFICE!!!
spill: USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION. VACUUM OR WET CLEAN IF DUST IS INVOLVED. ANY VACUUM SYSTEM SHOULD BE EQUIPPED W/ AN OUTLET "HEPA" FILTER TO PREVENT REINTRODUCING ASBESTOS FIBERS TO THE ATMOSPHERE.

appearance: VARIOUS COLORS, HONEY LIKE SUBSTANCE-CHARACTERISTIC ODOR
conditions_avoid: HIGH TEMPERATURES, SPARKS, AND OPEN FLAMES
decomposition_products: CO AND/OR C0*2
other_precautions: READ AND FOLLOW DIRECTIONS ON LABEL. DO NOT REUSE CONTAINERS.
protective_equipment: APRON AND WORK CLOTHING TO MINIMIZE EXPOSURE. EYE WASH STATION & SAFETY SHOWER RECOMMENDED.
respiratory_protection: IN HIGH VAPOR AREA, USE NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED RESPIRATOR WITH ORGANIC VAPOR CARTRIDGE. USE SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS IF VAPOR LEVELS EXCEED 1000 PPM.
ventilation: GEMERAL OR LOCAL EXHAUST RECOMMENDED TO CONTROL VAPORS BELOW 50% OF TLV.
disposal: DISOPSE OF I/A/W FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL REGULATIONS
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL.
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN A COOL, DRY, WELL-VENTILATED LOCATION, AWAY FROM ANY AREA WHERE THE FIRE HAZARD MAY BE ACUTE. KEEP CONTAINERS CLOSED WHEN NOT IN USE.
spill: SMALL SPILL: WIPE UP WITH RAGS OR TOWELS. LARGE SPILLS: WEAR NIOSH APPROVED RESPIRATOR. VENTILATE AREA. DIKE TO RETAIN FLUID. PUMP UP FREE LIQUID. RESIDUE WILL EVAPORATE QUICKLY. DO NOT FLUSH TO SEWER OR WATERWAY.

effects_overexposure_skin: irritation/burns.
first_aids_inhalation: remove to fresh air, provide cpr/oxygen if needed.
decomposition_products: HYDROGEN CHLORIDE, SULFUR DIOXIDE & OXIDES OF NITROGEN.
other_precautions: MATERIAL IS A SEVERE IRRITANT, AVOID CONTACT.
protective_equipment: IMPERVIOUS APRON/SHOES, EYE WASH FACILITY, EMERGENCY SHOWER.
respiratory_protection: NONE NORMALLY REQUIRED. USE NIOSH APPROVED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS IF TLV IS EXCEEDED OR WHEN SPRAYING OR USING IN CONFINED SPACES.
ventilation: USE LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION AT POINT OF DUST OR MIST RELEASE.
disposal: THIS IS A HAZARDOUS WASTE, RCRA D002. REPORTABLE QUANTITY 100 LBS. INCINERATE LIQUID AND CONTAMINATED LIQUID IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR A NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED, PRESSURE DEMAND, SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS & FULL PROTECTIVE CLOTHING. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL FIRE-EXPOSED CONTAINERS.
handling_storage: STORE IN A WELL VENTILATED AREA BELOW 131F/55C. DO NOT STORE IN STEEL CONTAINERS.
spill: WEAR PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. DIKE & ABSORB SPILL W/INERT MATERIAL/EARTH/SAND. SHOVEL ALL CONTAMINATED SOLIDS SUCH AS DIKING MATERIAL/ ABSORBENT/SOIL INTO CORROSION PROOF DRUMS. SEAL DRUMS BEFORE DISPOSA L. KEEP RUNOFF OUT OF MUNICIPAL WATERWAYS.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eyes/skin:moderately irritating.at elevated temperatures contact can result in burns.ingestion:low order of acute oral toxicity.inhalation:because of low volatility this product is not likely to be an inhalation hazard.
effects_overexposure_ingestion: ingestion:low order of acute oral toxicity.inhalation:because of low volatility this product is not likely to be an inhalation hazard.
effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation:because of low volatility this product is not likely to be an inhalation hazard.
effects_overexposure_skin: skin:moderately irritating.at elevated temperatures contact can result in burns.ingestion:low order of acute oral toxicity.inhalation:because of low volatility this product is not likely to be an inhalation hazard.
first_aids_eyes: flush with lots of water for 15 minutes holding lids open.get medical attention.hot product:immediately flush with cool water for 15 minutes & get medical attention.skin:remove contaminated cloth ing/shoes,wipe.flush with water,wash with soap & water.if irrit:get medical attention.hot product:immediately flush with cool water for 15 minutes.carefully remove clothing,if stuck,cut (see ing 5,6)
first_aids_skin: skin:remove contaminated cloth ing/shoes,wipe.flush with water,wash with soap & water.if irrit:get medical attention.hot product:immediately flush with cool water for 15 minutes.carefully remove clothing,if stuck,cut (see ing 5,6)
health_hazards_skin: skin sensitization (allergy) may be evidenced by rashes,especially hives.contact with product at elevated temperatures can result in thermal burns.
decomposition_products: CO,ALDEHYDES,ACIDS,OTHERS >500F.REACTION WITH SOME CURING AGENTS MAY PRODUCE CONSIDERABLE HEAT.RUN-AWAY (SEE ING 2,3)
eyes_protection: SAFETY GLASSES OR GOGGLES AS APPROPRIATE
other_precautions: MAY CAUSE IRRIT.AVOID CONTACT WITH EYES,SKIN.
protective_equipment: CHEMICAL RESISTANT CLOTHING AS REQUIRED TO MINIMIZE CONTACT.
respiratory_protection: NOT ORDINARILY REQUIRED.
ventilation: CONSULT LOCAL SAFETY/HEALTH AUTHORITIES IF ADDITIONAL GUIDANCE IS NEEDED .
disposal: DISPOSAL MUST BE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL,STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.COORDINATION WITH SUPPORTING INSTALLATION AND/OR MACOM ENVIRONMENTAL COORDINATION PRIOR TO DISPOSAL IS RECOMMENDED TO DETERMINE APPROPRIATE DISPOSAL METHODS .
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG,FOAM,DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
fire_fighting: WILL NOT BURN UNLESS PREHEATED.DO NOT ENTER CONFINED FIRE SPACE WITHOUT FULL BUNKER GEAR (HELMET WITH FACE SHIELD,BUNKER COATS,GLOVES & RUBBER BOOTS).(SEE SUPP)
handling_storage: STORE IN COOL,DRY PLACE.KEEP AWAY FROM OPEN FLAMES & HIGH TEMPERATURES.EVEN EMPTY CONTAINERS CAN CONTAIN HAZARDOUS RESIDUES.USE CAUTION.
spill: DOES NOT READILY BURN.LARGE SPILLS:CAUTION.WEAR RESPIRATOR & PROTECTIVE CLOTHING.SHUT OFF LEAK SOURCE IF SAFE.DIKE & CONTAIN.REMOVE WITH VACUUM TRUCKS OR PUMP TO STORAGE/SALVAGE VESSELS.FLUSH WITH WAT ER.LARGE/SMALL:ABSORB RESIDUE.DISPOSE OF PROPERLY.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation.
first_aids_eyes: eye contact: flush with water 15 minutes or until irritation subsides.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation.
appearance: PURPLE COLOR LIQUID WITH SWEET ESTER SOLVENT ODOR.
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE.

first_aids_eyes: flush with water and consult physician.skin:remove clothing and wash skin with soap and water.ingestion:drink 1 or 2 glasses of water to dilute.call a physician immediately.inhalation:if overcome by vapor,remove from exposure and callphysician.if breathing is irregular or stopped,start resuscitation,administer oxygen.

health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation of vapors:unconsciousness,coma.repeated overexposure to solvents/vapors will cause damage to liv,kid & general nervous system.liquid substance can be absorbed through intact skin in harmful amounts.propylene glycol monomethyl ether:repeated excessive exposure (inhalation) may cause lung,liver,kidney effects.
health_hazards_skin: skin in harmful amounts.propylene glycol monomethyl ether:repeated excessive exposure (inhalation) may cause lung,liver,kidney effects.
decomposition_products: OXIDES OF CARBON,TOXIC FUMES.
eyes_protection: SAFETY EYEWEAR TO PROTECT FROM SPLASH.
other_precautions: DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY.GROUND CNTRS WHEN POURING.AVOID FREE FALL IN EXCESS OF A FEW INCHES.DO NOT FLAME CUT/BRAZE/WELD W/O BUREAU OF MINES APPROVED VENT.ADD LABEL WARNINGS.HIGHER LEVELS OF VAP ARE REL EASED DURING BAKING OF PARTS (SEE SUPP)
protective_equipment: USE PROTECTIVE CREAM WHERE SKIN CONTACT IS LIKELY.PREVENT PROLONGED SKIN CONTACT TO CONTAMINATED CLOTHING.
respiratory_protection: IN OUTDOOR/OPEN AREA USE BUREAU OF MINES APPROVED MECH FILTER RESP TO REMOVE SOLID AIRBORNE PARTICLES OF OVERSPRAY DURING SPRAY APPLICATION.IN RESTRICTED VENT AREA,USE BUREAU OF MINES APPROVED CHEM-ME CH FILTERS DESIGNED TO REMOVE (SUP DA)
ventilation: PROVIDE GEN DILUTION OR LOC EXHAUST VENT IN VOLUME & PATTERN TO KEEP TLV OF MOST HAZARDOUS INGREDIENTS BELOW (SEE SUPP)
disposal: DISPOSAL MUST BE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL,STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.COORDINATION WITH SUPPORTING INSTALLATION AND/OR MACOM ENVIRONMENTAL COORDINATION PRIOR TO DISPOSAL IS RECOMMENDED TO DETERMINE APPROPRIATE DISPOSAL METHODS .
extinguishing_media: USE NATIONAL FIRE PROTECTION ASSOCIATION (NFPA) CLASS B EXTINGUISHERS (CARBON DIOXIDE,DRY CHEMICAL OR FOAM).
fire_fighting: WATER SPRAY MAY BE INEFFECTIVE.WATER MAY BE USED TO PREVENT PRESSURE BUILD-UP & POSSIBLE AUTOIGNITION/EXPLOSION IN EXTREME HEAT.FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERRED.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 120F,48.89C.STORE LARGE QUANTITIES IN BUILDINGS DESIGNED TO COMPLY WITH OSHA 1910.106.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION.AVOID BREATHING VAPORS.VENTILATE AREA.REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBENT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

effects_overexposure_skin: skin, or gets into eyes.
conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, HEAT BY WELDING OR CUTTING, WILL PRODUCE SMOKE, CARBON MONOXIDE AND CARBON DIOXIDE.
other_precautions: EMPTY CONTAINERS SHOULD NOT BE WASHED OR REUSED FOR ANY PURPOSE AND SHOULD BE GROUNDED & BONDED TO RECEIVING CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD, BRAZE OR CUT ON EMPTY CONTAINER. NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. DISPO SE AS HAZARDOUS WASTE, IGNITABLE, D001.
respiratory_protection: IN WELL VENTILATED AREAS, RESPIRATORY PROTECTION MAY NOT BE REQUIRED. IN RESTRICTED AREAS USE A NIOSH APPROVED CHEMICAL CARTRIDGE RESPIRATOR. FOR SPRAYING USE MECH PREFILTER. IN CONFINED AREAS USE NIO SH/MSHA APPR AIR SUPPLIED RESPIRATOR.
ventilation: DILUTE & LOCAL EXHAUST RECOMMENDED TO CONTROL CONCENTRATE OF HAZARDOUS INGREDIENTS.**
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN I/A/W FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL LAWS. INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA PERMITTED FACILITY. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS. OBSERVE PRECAUTIONS FOR DISP OF FLAMMABLE MATERIALS. CONTAMINATED ABSOR BENT MAY BE DISPOSED IN A HAZARD WASTE LANDFILL.
extinguishing_media: USE CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL TO EXTINGUISH FLAMMABLE LIQUID FIRES. POLYMER FOAM PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WATER MAY BE INEFFECTIVE BUT USED TO COOL EXPOSED CONTAINERS & PREVENT PRESS BUILDUP & POSSIBLE AUTO-IGNITE/EXPLOS. IF WATER USED, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERABLE.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 90 DEGREES F.
spill: KEEP SPECTATORS AWAY. ELIMINATE ALL IGNITE SOURCES, CONTAIN SPILL WITH INERT MATERIAL, TRANSFER LIQUID TO COVERED METAL CONTAINERS FOR DISPOSAL. USE ONLY NON-SPARK TOOLS. PREVENT CONTAMINATION OF SEWE RS, STREAMS & GROUNDWATER.

disposal: DISPOSAL MUST BE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL,STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.COORDINATION WITH SUPPORTING INSTALLATION AND/OR MACOM ENVIRONMENTAL COORDINATION PRIOR TO DISPOSAL IS RECOMMENDED TO DETERMINE APPROPRIATE DISPOSAL METHODS .
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG,FOAM,DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
fire_fighting: STANDARD TURNOUT GEAR WITH NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED SCBA .
handling_storage: KEEP CONTAINER CLOSED WHEN NOT IN USE.DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY.GROUND CONTAINERS WHEN POURING.AVOID FREE FALL OF LIQUID IN EXCESS OF FEW INCHES.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION.AVOID BREATHING VAPORS.VENTILATE AREA.REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBANT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL,STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.BEFORE ATTEMPT ING TO CLEAN UP,SEE INGREDIENT SECTION.

other_precautions: AVOID CONTACT WITH EYES AND SKIN. WASH THOROUGHLY AFTER HANDLING. LAUNDER CLOTHING BEFORE REUSE. AVOID INHALING MISTS. EMPTY CONTAINERS OF THIS PRODUCT MAY BE HAZARDOUS DUE TO THE RETENTION OF RESIDUE S. DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY.

respiratory_protection: NONE NORMALLY REQUIRED. IF WORKING IN CONFINED AREAS, IF EXCESSIVE MISTING IS EXPECTED OR IF EXPOSURE MAY OR DOES EXCEED RECOMMENDED PERMISSIBLE EXPOSURE LIMITS (PEL), WEAR NIOSH-APPROVED ORGANIC VAPO R RESPIRATOR.
ventilation: GENERAL ROOM VENTILATION SHOULD BE SUFFICIENT.
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN AN APPROPRIATE DISPOSAL FACILITY IN COMPLIANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS. REUSE IS RECOMMENDED. CONTAINS BARIUM. HAZARDOUS WASTE NUMBER: D005
extinguishing_media: WATER FOG, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL/CARBON DIOXIDE. DON'T USE DIRECT STREAM OF WATER. PRODUCT WILL FLOAT AND CAN BE REIGNITED.
fire_fighting: DO NOT ENTER ANY ENCLOSED OR CONFINED AREA WITHOUT PROPER PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT AND NIOSH-APPROVED SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS.
handling_storage: STORE IN COOL, DRY, VENTILATED PLACE AWAY FROM FLAMES AND STRONG OXIDIZERS. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN.
spill: PICK UP SPILL WITH INERT MATERIAL SUCH AS SAND, CLAY, EARTH. SHOVEL INTO CONTAINERS FOR DISPOSAL. PREVENT RUN-OFF TO ENTER WATERWAYS, SEWERS. THIS IS AN OIL. SPILLS INTO OR LEADING TO SURFACE WATER TH AT CAUSE A SHEEN MUST BE REPORTED: 800-424-8802.

protective_equipment: SAFETY SHOWER AND EYE WASH STATION NEAR WORK AREA.
respiratory_protection: USE A FULL FACE PIECE SUPPLIED AIR RESPIRATOR OR SELF CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS FOR CONCENTRATIONS GREATER THAN TLV.
ventilation: LOCAL AND MECHANICAL EXHAUST IF TLV IS EXCEEDED.VENTILATE SUMPS AND PITS WHERE VAPORS MAY COLLECT.
disposal: DISPOSAL MUST BE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL,STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS.COORDINATION WITH SUPPORTING INSTALLATION AND/OR MACOM ENVIRONMENTAL COORDINATION PRIOR TO DISPOSAL IS RECOMMENDED TO DETERMINE APPROPRIATE DISP METH .EVAPORATE OUTDOORS.
extinguishing_media: HALON 1301 IS A FIRE EXTINGUISHING MEDIA.
fire_fighting: SELF CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS TO PROTECT AGAINST VAPORIZED MATERIAL DECOMPOSITION PRODUCTS (BROMINE,FLUORINE,HALOGEN ACIDS AND CARBONYL HALIDES).
handling_storage: STORE CONTAINERS IN A CLEAN,DRY AREA.DO NOT HEAT ABOVE 125F,51.67C.
spill: VENTILATE AREA-ESPECIALLY LOW PLACES WHERE HEAVY VAPORS MAY COLECT.REMOVE OPEN FLAMES.

effects_overexposure_inhalation: inhalation may cause irritation of the respiratory tract, headaches, dizziness or drowsiness.
health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation may cause irritation of the respiratory tract, headaches, dizziness or drowsiness.
conditions_avoid: WILL REACT W/WATER OR WATER CONTAINING PRODUCT, GIVE OFF HEAT/FUMES. DON'T ALLOW WATER TO ENTER SEALED DRUM, MAY EXPLODE
decomposition_products: FUMES MAY CONTAIN CARBON MONOXIDE & OXIDES OF NITROGEN. MAY PRODUCE HAZARDOUS FUMES WHEN HEATED TO DECOMP AS IN WELDING.
eyes_protection: SAFETY EYEWARE TO PROTECT AGAINST SPLASH
other_precautions: MAKE SURE DRUM IS COMPLETELY EMPTY BEFORE ATTEMTING TO WELD OR BRAZE. DRUM SHOULD BE INDUSTRIALLY CLEANED PRIOR TO REUSE. DO NOT FLAME CUT, BRAZE OR WELD WITHOUT A NIOSH APPROVED RESPIRATOR OR APPROPR IATE VENTILATION.
respiratory_protection: DO NOT BREATHE VAPOR OR MIST. USE NIOSH/MSHA TC19C AIR LINE RESPIRATOR OR TC23C VAPOR/PARTICULATE RESPIRATOR IF ISOCYANATES ARE 10 X LESS THAN TLV.
ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION OR LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP TWA/LEL BELOW ACCEPTABLE LIMITS & TO REMOVE DECOMPOSITION PRODUCTS
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH LOCAL, STATE AND FEDERAL REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL OR CARBON DIOXIDE.
handling_storage: CONTAINERS SHOULD BE GROUNDED WHEN POURING. AVOID FREE FALL OF LIQUID IN EXCESS OF A FEW INCHES.
spill: REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. AVOID BREATHING VAPORS. VENTILATE AREA AND REMOVE WITH INERT ABSORBANT AND NON-SPARKING TOOLS.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.

other_precautions: AS MANUFACTURED, LOCKED-IN ASBESTOS DOES NOT PRESENT A HAZARD. ONLY WHEN THE ITEM IS SUBJECTED TO ABRASIVE ACTIONS & DUST IS GENERATED, THEN ASBESTOS FIBERS MAY BE RELEASED & BECOME AIRBORNE.
protective_equipment: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND, AND THE GUIDANCE SET FORTH BY YOUR SAFETY OFFICE OR IH PERSONNEL
protective_gloves: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND.

other_precautions: WEAR LOW-STATIC OR PROPERLY GROUNDED SHOES.KEEP CONTAINERS CLOSED WHEN NOT IN USE.
protective_equipment: PROTECTIVE CLOTHING AS NEEDED TO PREVENT CONTACT DURING HANDLING.
respiratory_protection: DURINGSPILLS OR CLEANUP ACTIVITIES, WEAR NIOSH APPROVED ORGANIC VAPOR RESPIRATOROR EQUVALENT OFR SUPPLEMENTAL PROTECTION WHERE NEEDED.
ventilation: USE LOCAL AND GENERAL VENTILATION TO MAINTAIN VAPOR LEVELS WITHIN ESTABLISHED THRESHOLD LIMIT VALUES.
disposal: RECLAMATION OR INCINERATION IN A PERMITTED HAZAR- DOUS WASTE FACILITY CAPABLE OF MEETING APPLICABLE REGULATORY REQUIREMENTS FOR DESTRUCTION OR REMOVALIS PREFERRED.OTHERWISE,DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH APPLICABLE REGULATIONS.
extinguishing_media: CARBON DIOXIDE,FOAM,OR DRY CHEMICALS
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD BE EQUIPPED WITH FULL PROTECTIVE GEAR AND SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS.
handling_storage: COMBUSTIBLE LIQUID,KEEP AWAY FROM HEAT,SPARKS,OPENFLAME,PREVENT ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION.GROUND CON- TAINERS SECURELY WHEN TRANSFERRING CONTENTS.

effects_overexposure_eyes: irritation, redness, tearing skin: prolonged or repeated contact can causemoderate irrit.

conditions_avoid: FLAMMABLE LIQUID PRODUCT. STRONG OXIDIZING AGENTS.
decomposition_products: MAY FORM TOXIC MATERIALS, CARBON DIOXIDE AND CARBON MONOXIDEVARIOUS HYDROCARBONS.
protective_equipment: TO PREVENT REPEATED OR PROLONGED SKIN CONTACT, WEAR IMPERVIOUS CLOTHING AND BOOTS.
respiratory_protection: USE A NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED AIR SUPPLIED RESP OR OSHA REG MUST BE A NEGATIVE PRES SURE TYPE, WHEN EXPOSURE LIMTS ARE EXCEEDED, TO MAINTAIN OR IMPLEMENT PROPER VENTILATION WHEN USING PRODUCT.
ventilation: PROVIDE SUFFICIENT MECHANICAL (GENERAL AND/OR LOCAL EXHAUST)TO MAINTAIN EXPOSURE BELOW TLV LEVELS PERMITTED.
disposal: DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL LOCAL, STATE ANDFEDERAL REGULATIONS. SINCE EMPTIED CONTAINERS RETAIN PRODUCT RESIDUES ALL CONTAINERS OF THIS PROD. MAY BE HAZARDOUS.
extinguishing_media: REGULAR FOAM OR CARBON DIOXIDE OR DRY CHEMICAL
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WITH A FULL FACEPIECE OPERATED IN THE POSITIVE PRESSURE DEMAND MODE WHEN FIGHTING FIRES.
spill: SMLL: ABSORB LIQUID ON PAPAER, VERMICULITE, FLOOR ABSORB/ABSORB MATERIAL. LRG: ELIM ALL ING. SOURCESSTOP SPILL AT SOURCE DIKE AREA TO PREVNT SPREADINGPUMP LIQ. TO SALVGE TANK. REMANING USE SAND/CLAY/ EARTH/FLOOR ABSORBENT AND SHOVEL INTO CONTAINERS.

conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, INCLUDING WHEN HEATED BY WELDING/CUTTING, WILL PRO-DUCE SMOKE/CARBON MONOXIDE/CARBON DIOXIDE/OXIDES OF LEAD.
other_precautions: DO NOT BREATHE SANDING DUST OR REUSE EMPTY CONT. DO NOT TAKE INTERN. CONT'ER S/BGROUNDED AND BONDED TO THE RECEIVING CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD/BRAZE OR CUT CONT'R.NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. DRUM IS NOT A PRESSURE VESSEL. CLOSE AFTER EA USE.
protective_equipment: AS REQUIRED TO PREVENT SKIN CONTACT.
respiratory_protection: WELL VENTILATED AREA-RESP NOT REQ. RESTRICTED VENT-NIOSH CHEMICAL CARTRIDGE MAY BE REQ. IF SPRAYING, MECH PREFILTER MAY BE REQ. IF TLV ARE EXCEEDED, USE A PROP FITTED NIOSH/MSHA RESP W/APPROP PROTECTI ON FACTOR. SEE OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134.
ventilation: PROVIDE DILUT/LOCAL EXH VENT TO KEEP CONCENT OF HAZ INGRID BELOW EXPOSURE LMT STD. REMOVE PROD GEN-WELD/CUT/BRAZ OBJECT
disposal: INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA PERMITTED FACILITY. DISPOSEONLY IAW FED/STATE/LOCAL REGS. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS. OBSERVE PRECAUTIONS FOR DIS- POSAL OF FLAMMABLE MAT'S. CONTAMINATED ABOSRBENT MAY BE DISPOSED IN A HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL.
extinguishing_media: USE CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. WATER TO COOL CONT TO PREVENT POSSIBLE AUTO-IGNITION OR EXPLOSION. IF WATER IS USED, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERABLE.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 95F. STORE LARGE QUANTITIES IN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29CFR1910.106.
spill: ELIM ALL IGNITION SOURCES. DIKE/CONTAIN SPILL WITHINERT MAT'L. TRANSFER LIQ'S/ABSORBENT DIKING MAT'LIN COVERED METAL CONT'S FOR RECOVERY/DISPOSAL. USEONLY NON-SPARKING TOOLS. PREVENT CONTAM OF SEWERS/ STREAMS/GROUNDWATER W/SPILLED MAT'L/USED ABSORBENT

protective_equipment: NOT LIKELY TO BE NEEDED.

extinguishing_media: USE NFPA CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.

effects_overexposure_eyes: eye contact: irritation, burning, tearing, redness & swelling.
first_aids_eyes: immediately flush with plenty of water for 15 minutes.
decomposition_products: THERMAL DECOMPOSITION MAY YIELD CARBON MONOXIDE AND/OR CARBON DIOXIDE.

other_precautions: EMPTY CONTAINERS RETAIN RESIDUE AND CAN BE DANGEROUS. DO NOT PRESSURIZE, CUT, WELD, ETC. ON THE CONTAINER. BEFORE WORKING ON OR IN TANKS WHICH CONTAIN OR HAVE CONTAINED THIS PRODUCT, REFER TO OSHA RE GULATIONS AND/OR ANSI Z49.1 PERTAINING TO CLEANING, REPAIRING, WELDING OR OTHER CONTEMPLATED OPERATI ONS.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH FOUNTAIN. NEOPRENE APRON.
protective_gloves: PLASTIC OR HYDROCARBON INSOLUBLE RUBBER GLOVES
respiratory_protection: THE USE OF RESPIRATORY PROTECTION IS ADVISED WHEN CONCENTRATIONS EXCEED THE ESTABLISHED EXPOSURE LIMITS. DEPENDING ON THE AIRBORNE CONCENTRATION, USE A RESPIRATOR OR GAS MASK WITH APPROPRIATE CARTRID GES AND CANNISTERS (NOISH APPROVED, IF AVAILABLE) OR SUPPLIED AIR EQUIPMENT.
ventilation: CURRENT VENTILATION IS NOT ADEQUATE TO MAINTAIN AIRBORNE CONCENTRATION BELOW THE ESTABLISHED EXPOSURE LIMITS; VENTILATION OR EXHAUST SYSTEMS MAY BE REQUIRED.
disposal: ALL CONTAINERS SHOULD BE DIPOSED OF IN AN ENVIRONMENTALLY SAFE MANNER AND IN ACCORDANCE WITH GOVERNMENT REGULATIONS - LOCAL, STATE, AND FEDERAL AGENCIES.
extinguishing_media: SMALL FIRES: DRY CHEMICAL, CARBON DIOXIDE OR FOAM. LARGE FIRES: DRY CHEMICAL OR FOAM. WATER MAY BE INEFFECTIVE ON THIS PRODUCT.
fire_fighting: THE USE OF SCBA IS RECOMMENDED FOR FIRE FIGHTERS. WATER SPAY MAY BE USEFUL TO MINIMIZE VAPORS AND COOLING CONTAINERS BUT USE CAUTION TO PREVENT SPREADING OF BURNING LIQUID BY THE COOLING WATER.
handling_storage: KEEP CONTAINERS TIGHTLY CLOSED, COOL, DRY & AWAY FROM SOURCES OF IGNITION. USE & STORE THIS PRODUCT WITH ADEQUATE VENTILATION. DO NOT PRESSURIZE, CUT, WELD, BRAZE, SOLDER, DRILL, GRIND OR EXPOSE SUC H CONTAINERS TO HEAT, FLAMES, OR SPARKS.
spill: STAY UPWIND & AWAY FROM SPILL. KEEP ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION AND HOT METAL SURFACES AWAY FROM SPILL. IF SPILL IS INDOORS, VENTILATE AREA OF SPILL. FOAM MAY BE USED TO SUPPRESS VAPORS. KEEP OUT OF D RAINS, SEWERS OR WATERWAYS. USE SAND OR INERT MATERIAL TO DAM OR CONTAIN SPILL. DO NOT FLUSH AREA WITH WATER; USE ABSORBENT PADS.

decomposition_products: CARBON DIOXIDE, CARBON MONOXIDE, NITROGEN OXIDES.
other_precautions: EMPTY CONTAINERS CONTAIN PRODUCT RESIDUE. DO NOT REUSE EXCEPT FOR STORAGE OR SHIPMENT OF ORIGINAL PRODUCT. REMOVE ALL PRODUCT RESIDUE AND PUNCTURE OR OTHERWISE DESTROY EMPTY CONTAINER BEFORE DISPOSAL.
protective_equipment: EYE WASH STATION.
protective_gloves: COTTON GLOVES OVER THIN LATEX GLOVES.
respiratory_protection: NOT NEEDED WITH ADEQUATE VENTILATION. OTHERWISE, USE NIOSH/MSHA APPROVED RESPIRATOR IF DUST IS THE ONLY CONCERN. THERE IS NO AIR PURIFYING RESPIRATOR APPROVED FOR ISOSORBIDE DINITRATE. ORGANIC CARTRID GES ARE NOT ADEQUATE.
ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST.
disposal: DISCARDED PRODUCT IS NOT A HAZARDOUS WASTE UNDER RCRA, 40CFR261. DISPOSE OF IN ACCORDANCE WITH ALL APPLICABLE FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS
extinguishing_media: USE CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, DRY CHEMICAL, OR WATER FOG.
fire_fighting: WEAR SCBA AND FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. USE BARRICADE DUE TO POSSIBILITY OF EXPLOSION. IF FIRE CANNOT BE CONTROLLED IN EARLY STAGES, EVACUATE TO SAFE DISTANCE.
handling_storage: AVOID BREATHING DUST. PREVENT SKIN CONTACT.
spill: WEAR SKIN PROTECTION DURING CLEANUP. SWEEP UP AND RECOVER. WET MATERIAL WITH WATER IN A PLASTIC BAG. WHEN TABLETS BEGIN TO DISINTEGRATE, DISCARD WITH GENERAL TRASH. WASH RESIDUE WITH WATER AND FLUSH T O A SEWER SERVICED BY WASTEWATER TREATMENT FACILTY

effects_overexposure_eyes: eye: potential irritation from airborne dust; ingest: n/k.

other_precautions: AS MANUFACTURED, LOCKED-IN ASBESTOS DOES NOT PRESENT A HAZARD. ONLY WHEN THE ITEM IS SUBJECTED TO ABRASIVE ACTIONS & DUST IS GENERATED, THEN ASBESTOS FIBERS MAY BE RELEASED & BECOME AIRBORNE.
protective_equipment: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND, AND THE GUIDANCE SET FORTH BY YOUR SAFETY OFFICE OR IH PERSONNEL
protective_gloves: AS REQUIRED FOR TASK AT HAND.

ventilation: LOCAL EXHAUST IS RECOMMENDED IN SITUATIONS WHERE DUST IS GENERATED BY ABRASIVE ACTIONS, ABRASION OR OTHER MEANS.
disposal: DUST SHOULD BE HANDLED AS A HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANT I/A/W 40CFR61 SUBPART "M" PERTAINING TO ASBESTOS. USE LANDFILLS APPROVED FOR ASBESTOS DISPOSAL. NOTE IF ITEM UNDER CONSIDERATION FOR DISPOSAL IS "FRIABLE OR NON-FRIABLE".
extinguishing_media: MATERIAL IS NOT FLAMMABLE ; USE MEDIA APPROPRIATE FOR SURROUNDING FIRE.
fire_fighting: COMBUSTION PRODUCTS OF THIS MATERIAL MAY BE TOXIC. USE A SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WHEN FIGHTING FIRES INVOLVING CHEMICAL PRODUCTS.
handling_storage: HANDLE IN A MATTER TO MINIMIZE FORMATION OR RETENTION OF AIRBORNE DUST. USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION FOR TASK AT HAND. CHECK W/YOUR SAFETY OFFICE!!!
spill: USE PROPER PERSONAL PROTECTION. VACUUM OR WET CLEAN IF DUST IS INVOLVED. ANY VACUUM SYSTEM SHOULD BE EQUIPPED W/ AN OUTLET "HEPA" FILTER TO PREVENT REINTRODUCING ASBESTOS FIBERS TO THE ATMOSPHERE.

health_hazards_inhalation: inhalation of vapors may cause/mists may cause irritation of nose, throat & respiratory tract.
decomposition_products: CARBON MONOXIDE, CARBON DIOXIDE AND OTHER UNIDENTIFIED COMPONENTS ARE FORMED ON COMBUSTION.
other_precautions: NO INFORMATION GIVEN ON MSDS BY SUPPLIER.
protective_equipment: OTHER CLOTHING AS REQUIRED TO MINIMIZE CONTACT.

ventilation: NO INFORMATION GIVEN ON MSDS BY SUPPLIER
disposal: DISPOSE AS HAZARDOUS WASTE D005 (BASED ON BARIUM CONTENT), UNLESS EXTRACTION RESULTS ARE LESS THAN EPA LIMITS.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG, CARBON DIOXIDE, FOAM, OR DRY CHEMICAL. DO NOT USE DIRECT STREAM OF WATER; OIL WILL FLOAT & MAY REIGNITE.
fire_fighting: DO NOT ENTER ENCLOSED SPACE WITHOUT FULL BUNKER GEAR INCLUDING POSITIVE PRESSURE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN A COOL, DRY, WELL VENTILATED AREA. PROTECT CONTAINERS FROM HEAT AND FLAMES.
spill: MAY BURN. USE CAUTION. WEAR PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT. SHUT OFF LEAK IF W/O RISK. DIKE & CONTAIN. REMOVE WITH VACUUM TRUCK OR PUMP TO STORAGE/SALVAGE VESSELS. SOAK UP REMAINDER WITH SAND, CLAY, ETC. FLUSH AREA W/ WATER. SMALL SPILL: ABSORB WITHABSORBENT.

conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, INCLUD WHEN HEATED BY WELDING/CUTTING, WILL PRODUCESMOKE/CARBON MONOXIDE-DIOXIDE/OXIDES OF NITROGEN & LEAD.
other_precautions: DO NOT BREATHE SANDING DUST OR REUSE EMPTY CONT. DO NOT TAKE INTERN. CONT'ER S/BGROUNDED AND BONDED TO THE RECEIVING CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD/BRAZE OR CUT CONT'R.NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. DRUM IS NOT A PRESSURE VESSEL. CLOSE AFTER EA USE.
protective_equipment: EYEWASH FACILITY, SAFETY SHOWER. AS REQUIRED TO PREVENT SKIN CONTACT.
respiratory_protection: WELL VENTILATED AREA-RESP NOT REQ. RESTRICTED VENT-NIOSH CHEMICAL CARTRIDGE MAY BE REQ. IF SPRAYING, MECH PREFILTER MAY BE REQ. IF TLF ARE EXCEEDED, USE A PROP FITTED NIOSH/MSHA RESP W/APPROP PROTECTI ON FACTOR. SEE OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134.
ventilation: PROVIDE DILUTION/LOCAL EXHAUST VENTILATION TO KEEP CONCEN- TRATIONS OF HAZARDOUS INGRID BELOW EXPOSURE LIMITS STATED.
disposal: INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA PERMITTED FACILITY. DISPOSEONLY IAW FED/STATE/LOCAL REGS. DO NOT INCINERATE CLOSED CONTAINERS. OBSERVE PRECAUTIONS FOR DIS- POSAL OF FLAMMABLE MAT'S. CONTAMINATED ABSORBENT MAY BE DISPOSED IN A HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL.
extinguishing_media: USE NFPA CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. WATER TO COOL CONT TO PREVENT POSSIBLE AUTO-IGNITION OR EXPLOSION. IF WATER IS USED, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERABLE.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 95F. STORE LARGE QUANTITIES IN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29CFR1910.106.
spill: ELIM ALL IGNITION SOURCES. DIKE/CONTAIN SPILL WITHINERT MAT'L. TRANSFER LIQ'S/ABSORBENT DIKING MAT'LIN COVERED METAL CONT'S FOR RECOVERY/DISPOSAL. USEONLY NON-SPARKING TOOLS. PREVENT CONTAM OF SEWERS/ STREAMS/GROUNDWATER W/SPILLED MAT'L/USED ABSORBENT

first_aids_inhalation: remove to fresh air, call a physician.
health_hazards_inhalation: vapor is heavier than air and can cause suffocation by reducing oxygen available for breathing.
conditions_avoid: HIGH TEMPERATURES, SPARKS, AND OPEN FLAMES
decomposition_products: DECOMPOSED BY HIGH TEMPERATURES (OPEN FLAMES, GLOWING METAL SURFACES, ETC.) FORMING HYDROCHLORIC AND HYDROFLUORIC ACIDS.
other_precautions: AVOID BREATHING VAPOR, LIQUID CONTACT WITH EYES, SKIN OR CLOTHING. TANK-CLEANING PERSONNEL SHOULD USE ONLY FORMAL TANK ENTRY PROCEDURE BASED ON RECOGNIZED SAFETY PRINCIPLES. EMPTY CONTAINERS MAY CONTA IN PRODUCT RESIDUES/VAPORS.
protective_equipment: USE IMPERVIOUS CLOTHING IF THERE IS REPEATED OR PROLONGED CONTACT WITH LIQUID.
respiratory_protection: NONE REQUIRED FOR ADEQUATELY VENTED WORK SITUATIONS. FOR ACCIDENTAL OR NON-VENTILATED SITUATIONS, USE A SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS OR SUPPLIED-AIR RESPIRATOR, APPROVED BY NIOSH.
ventilation: PROVIDE LOCAL EXHAUST AT FILLING ZONES AND OTHER OPERATING SPACES WHERE LEAKAGE IS PROBABLE. MECHANICAL FOR OTHER.
disposal: COMPLY WITH FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS. REMOVE TO A PERMITTED WASTE DISPOSAL FACILITY.
extinguishing_media: USE WATER FOG OR WATER SPRAY
fire_fighting: FIRE FIGHTERS SHOULD USE NIOSH APPROVED SCBA & FULL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT WHEN FIGHTING CHEMICAL FIRE. USE WATER SPRAY TO COOL NEARBY CONTAINERS EXPOSED TO FIRE.
handling_storage: STORE IN A CLEAN, COOL, DRY AND WELL-VENTILATED AREA OF LOW FIRE RISK. PROTECT CONTAINERS FROM PHYSICAL DAMAGE AND KEEP CLOSED.
spill: VENTILATE AREA. DO NOT FLUSH INTO SEWERS. DIKE SPILL. COLLECT ON ABSORBENT MATERIAL AND TRANSFER TO STEEL DRUMS FOR RECOVERY OR DISPOSAL. COMPLY WITH FEDERAL, STATE AND LOCAL REGULATIONS ON REPORTING RELEASES.

other_precautions: GROUND CONTAINER DURING STORAGE AND TRANSFER OPERATIONS.

spill: EVACUATE NON-ESSENTIAL PERSONNEL. VENTILATE & REMOVE ALL SOURCES OF IGNITION. COVER SPILL WITH ABSORBENT MATERIAL. NOTIFY AUTHORITIES. TRANSFER TO CONTAINERS FOR RECOVERY OR DISPOSAL.

first_aids_eyes: flush with water for 15 minutes.
health_hazards_eyes: eye & skin irritation: high concentrations may cause acute central nervous system depression characterized by headache, dizziness, nausea & confusion.
health_hazards_skin: skin irritation: high concentrations may cause acute central nervous system depression characterized by headache, dizziness, nausea & confusion.
conditions_avoid: AVOID EXCESSIVE HEAT AND SOURCES OF IGNITION.
decomposition_products: BURNING, WELDING & CUTTING WILL PRODUCE SMOKE, CARBON MONOXIDE & CARBON DIOXIDE.
other_precautions: DO NOT TAKE INTERNALLY. CLOSE CONTAINER AFTER EACH USE. DO NOT BREATH SANDING DUST. DO NOT REUSE CONTAINER. DO NOT WELD, BRAZE OR CUT ON EMPTY CONTAINER. NEVER USE PRESSURE TO EMPTY. CONTAINERS SHOULD BE GROUNDED & BONDED TO EACH OTHER.
protective_equipment: NOT LIKELY TO BE NEEDED
respiratory_protection: RESPIRATORS RECOMMENDED WITH THIS PRODUCT DURING & AFTER THE ADDITION OF CATALYST: PROPERLY FITTED POSITIVE PRESSURE (TC 19C NIOSH/MSHA) WHILE EXPOSED. IF NOT AVAILABLE USE VAPOR PARTICULATE, THAT IS EFFECTIVE FOR ISOCYANATE VAPORS.
ventilation: GENERAL DILUTION/LOCAL EXHAUST VENT IN SUFFICIENT VOLUME & PATTERN TO MAINTAIN CONCENTRATIONS OF HAZARDOUS SUBSTANCES
disposal: DISPOSE IN ACCORDANCE WITH FEDERAL, STATE & LOCAL LAWS. INCINERATE ONLY IN EPA FACILITY. DISPOSE IN A HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL. RCRA CLASSIFICATION WOULD BE D001. ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARD, NONE KNOWN.
extinguishing_media: CLASS B FIRE EXTINGUISHERS. POLYMER FOAM IS PREFERRED FOR LARGE FIRES.
fire_fighting: WEAR SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS. WATER MAY BE USED TO COOL EXPOSED CONTAINERS TO PREVENT AUTO-IGNITION OR EXPLOSION, FOG NOZZLES ARE PREFERRED.
handling_storage: DO NOT STORE ABOVE 95F. STORE LARGE QUANTITIES IN COMPLIANCE WITH OSHA 29 CFR 1910.106.
spill: ELIMINATE ALL IGNITION SOURCES. DIKE & CONTAIN SPILL WITH INERT MATERIAL. RECOVERY OR DISPOSAL IN A COVERED METAL CONTAINER, USE NON-SPARKING TOOLS. PREVENT CONTAMINATION OF SEWERS, STREAMS & GROUND W ATERS.

fire_fighting: COMBUSTION PRODUCTS OF THIS MATERIAL MAY BE TOXIC. USE A SELF-CONTAINED BREATHING APPARATUS WHEN FIGHTING FIRES INVOLVING CHEMICAL PRODUCTS.
